name: Brittany Noble
bio: Mom & national award-winning TV news reporter inspiring you to share your story ✨ @wishtv

social_posts.post_text:
May you be filled with joy, love and peace. 🫶🏾

#joy #peace #happiness #happy #thankful #grateful #loveyourself #loveyou #love #joyfulliving #happythoughts
Happy New Year Family. 🫶🏾🙌🏾
Keep Going. 🖤 Never Give Up.
I am so grateful for the opportunity to  visit #nyc and speak on the @linkedin show about authenticity, code switching and mentorship.
I anchored my first show on @wishtv8 today 🙌🏾
You will always be my baby ❤️👩‍👦
Happy Monday 💙 I hope your week is off to a great start. ✨
After a five year hiatus, I anchored 5 hours of news today 🙌🏾 I am preparing for another 5 tomorrow morning 🫶🏾 I hope you’ll join us on @wishtv8
Women supporting women 👸🏾 I’m loving the vibe in #Indianapolis 🖤 Last night newsies from local tv stations met up to welcome me to #Indiana 🥂
I am incredibly grateful for the opportunity to share stories on WISH. If you ever have something that you want to share on the news, send me a message. 💌 I would love to help. ❤️
I am blessed to call @iamalexisrogers my sister, friend and colleague. You are light ✨ Happy Birthday 🫶🏾
Today we celebrate love ✨ Nita’s youngest gradaughter exchanged vows today. 🖤Congratulations Matt & @destinyj_xo 💍
Everyone has a story to tell ✨

Today on @wishtv8 ✨ The @ncadv defines #domesticviolence as the willful intimidation, physical assault, battery, sexual assault, and/or other abusive behavior as part of a systematic pattern of power and control perpetrated by one intimate partner against another. It includes physical violence, sexual violence, threats, economic, and emotional/psychological abuse.
Meet some of the weekend team❣️

It’s C.R.O.W.N. Day 👑

✨

In 2019, my son and I traveled to Washington D.C to speak with lawmakers about the importance of @thecrownact I wanted to be strong but inside I felt weak. I was afraid of the consequences we’d face as a result of me sharing my experience. Fast forward to today, 23 states have created a respectful and open world for natural hair.

Members of @dstinc1913 are in town for their national convention. They are giving away more than $50,000 worth of goods to Indy youth. I got a peak at the school supplies in the backpacks that the @indyurbanleague777 will pass out to students on Saturday.
“The things which are impossible with men are possible with God.” ✨ Luke 18:27

I never imagined I’d be a TV reporter with locs but tomorrow I’ll step away from the news desk to have a conversation about hair with my sisters in Birmingham. I met my mentor @tvnewslady in the student project room at my first NABJ convention. I felt so much love that I now attend the event annually. I have been on a deeply personal hair journey and both @tasharaparker and @iyanilenice.tv have always cheered me on. They even created safe spaces for women with curly hair. 🥰 Family, I can’t wait to see you and I hope you’ll join us for the #crownonair panel at #nabj23 ✨
Today I caught up w/ some of my mentors, co-workers and mentees at the #nabj23 national convention. 😍🥰 I’m headed back to Indianapolis, until Chicago 🙏🏾✌🏾😘 🫶🏾❤️🖤 #BlackJournalistsMatter
August has been good to us. Let’s make it a September to remember ✨ #libraseason 🙏🏾 RIP #MikeBrown

There is so much love among the creatives  in Indianapolis. The best part of the @butterartfair is that the artists sold more than $200,000 worth of art and organizers @ganggangculture will not take a profit. 🖼️
I almost floated away in a hot air balloon today. The weather was awful so I decided to go inside the balloon instead. 🎈 Jupiter Lights Balloon Festival.
Thank you God for 37 years ✨♎️
null
Happy New Year ✨
Our Martin Luther King Jr event at the @walkertheatre is sold out tomorrow but you can still DM questions to ask @rolandsmartin ✨
